                <h1>Rosa Parks: The Woman Who Changed History</h1>
                <p>Rosa Parks, known as the "mother of the civil rights movement," made history on December 1, 1955, by refusing to give up her bus seat to a white passenger in Montgomery, Alabama. Her courageous act sparked the Montgomery Bus Boycott and became a symbol of resistance against racial segregation, inspiring future generations to fight for equality.</p>
